    "However, not all AI-based tools are directly associated with ICALL, they are diversified into multiple forms and tools as follows; Adaptive Educational System (Triantafillou et al. 2003), Intelligent Educational System (Cumming et al. 1993) Intelligent Personal Assistant (Rahman and Tomy 2023; Yang et al. 2022) Intelligent Tutoring System (Slavuj et al. 2015), Natural language processing (Nagata 2013), Machine translation tools (Briggs 2018), Chatbots (Jeon 2021; Dokukina and Gumanova 2020), AI writing assistants (Gayed et al. 2022; Godwin-Jones 2022), AI-powered language learning software (Pokrivčáková 2019) and Intelligent Virtual Reality (Ma 2021).",
